-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/nigeria-delays-power-companies-sale-process-businessday-says.html
Nigeria â€™s privatization agency is yet
to approve applications received by a March 4 deadline from
groups interested in bidding for state-owned power companies,
 BusinessDay  said, citing the director-general of the agency,
Bola Onagoruwa.  The institution has evaluated the applications and is
waiting for feedback from the presidency, the Lagos-based
newspaper cited Onagoruwa as saying, without giving details.  The agency received 174 applications from investors and
concessionaires interested in acquiring four thermal stations
and two hydro stations, and 157 from those interested in buying
11 distribution companies, BusinessDay reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
